data.value:
CHAIN OF COMMAND:
1. Titan holds STRATEGIC operational control over entire mission.
2. Alpha-Actual holds TACTICAL operational control over Alpha and Wolf in the field.
-This means, Titan can direct JMS-34 towards MACRO objectives, while Alpha-Actual will control all movements at a tactical level on the ground.
2a. Succession: Titan > Alpha-Actual > Wolf-Actual > Alpha

TITAN NOTES:
1. The main role of Titan is to provide recon as well as strategic operational control of the mission.
2. The secondary role of Titan is to provide aerial support designated in a proper 'Call for Fire' from a designated JTAC.
2a. This includes:
-Firemissions from the MQ-12 falcon drone.
-Requirements: Laser designation, confirmation of JTAC codeword.

-1x CAS airstrike by relaying the 'Call for Fire' to higher.
-Requirements: 10Digit grid reference, laser designation, direction of strike, confirmation of JTAC codeword.

data.value:
1. JMS-34 will proceed out of Spartan AFB to Coyote's last known position following MSR Redwood through MSR Pine.
-MSR Birch will be avoided UNLESS explicit authorization is given to JMS-34 to proceed along route.
2. JMS-34 will investigate the site of Coyote's last known position and attempt to locate personnel and the WMD to get them safely to Spartan AFB.
3. If locating WMD and personnel at last known position proves unsuccessful, JMS-34 will attempt to track down the personnel and equipment Coyote was transporting.

Attribute4.expression: _this setVariable ['Subject',_value,true];

data.value:
OBJECTIVES:
1. Follow appropriate MSRs to approximate last known position and investigate the disappearance of Coyote.
-If the convoy was ambushed/destroyed, recover survivors and WMD and call for recovery helo.
-If WMD is NOT recovered at site, you MUST follow any lead to recover it.

RULES OF ENGAGEMENT:
1. Weapons free in 'Known Insurgent Territory'. If tango has a weapon, you are free to fire.
2. Elsewhere, target MUST be identified to be a threat BEFORE engagement.
2a. Opportunity, Capability, Intent.
-Civilians that are watching you DO NOT meet the criteria.
-Civilians placing IEDs DO meet the criteria.

data.value:
At approximately 0230 local time, a NATO JTF transport convoy, callsign Coyote, ceased providing radio contact with Spartan AFB.  
Their arrival time was supposed to be 0415 and they have yet to show. JTF-3 Commander has authorized one JTF Mechanized Squad (JMS-34) to  
depart Spartan AFB at approximately 0500 to search for the whereabouts of Coyote and if found recover survivors as well as the WMD  
and get them both airlifted back to Spartan AFB.
